  "body": "### Description\r\nCatch-All - Critical transaction exception / unable to load trie node\r\n\r\nReference - #4779, #4768, #4434 \r\n\r\nMaybe related #4379, #4784\r\n\r\nCritical Exception processing transaction \r\n            - Error on new payload call with submitted transaction, snapshot concurrency \r\n\r\nInstability around trie node unable to load:\r\n        - [Discord Context 1](https://discord.com/channels/697535391594446898/888098626264502302/1049531467983761449) \r\n        - [Discord Context 2](https://discord.com/channels/697535391594446898/888098626264502302/1048975986445791242)\r\n        - [Discord Context 3](https://discord.com/channels/697535391594446898/888098626264502302/1049531467983761449)\r\n\r\nUser reported experiencing unable to load trie node still after disabling snapshots `--Xbonsai-use-snapshots`. This user was able to fix their issue by downgrading to 22.10.2. [Context](https://discord.com/channels/697535391594446898/888098626264502302/1050211939567030423) \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Removal of concurrency \r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Process certain transactions with an incomplete world state\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\nNo error for valid blocks\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\nInfrequent errors when submitting user tx and just processing blocks\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\nInfrequent \r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: 22.10.2",
